{"id": "duc04-testb-49:15#46", "contents": "However, Primakov did acknowledge the need to take steps to prevent the outflow of dollars from Russia, which he referred to as the \"dollar drain.\" He cited statistics showing that Russian companies had stashed around $2.5 billion outside the country in September alone. Primakov emphasized the importance of foreign investment in helping Russia minimize its losses from the current economic crisis, particularly in the real production sector. He expressed interest in long-term investments, stating that short-term operations were not beneficial for either Russia or foreign investors."}
